channel.title: Kind of a stupid question but
channel.description:
Hey I know this might seem stupid to you but I just never figured it out.
What do all of the like versions of servers mean?
for example.
what does a 317 mean a 374 or w.e its called a 474 or something like that a 503 a 508 and a 525? I dont really understand all of the versions nor do I even know if those are what they are called. Can someone explain this all to me?

item.title: Kind of a stupid question but
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

[quote=“Lin, post:3, topic:278294”][quote author=Newty link=topic=367290.msg2782761#msg2782761 date=1242171145]
They are the versions of the Runescape client.
[/quote]And cache.[/quote]

Not technically. We just associate the two. There are at least three times more updates on the cache than the client. They only increment the client’s version when it’s modified. And it’s only modified when they make some major changes.

Read full topic
